track_title: From the A702 to the summit

track_notes: If main walkers car park closed the overflow car park in close by. Activated August 2021.
track_title: Shorter route from Swanston Golf Club overflow car park

track_notes:
Route from the Hunters Tryst end of the Lothian Buses #5 and #27 routes.

Dreghorn link connects to the bypass so be aware of traffic.

The rest of the route is clear and easy, and mostly gravel path. There are a few gates and stiles, and a small stream to cross with well embedded rocks. It is also quite sheltered in the valley between Allermuir and Capelaw hills.

The turnoff to the northeast near the summit is signposted.
track_title: Hunter's Tryst bus stop to Allermuir

track_notes: There was plenty of car parking at Boghall. Note there is a 2m hight restriction at the car park. Follow the path round the back of the buildings. Then it is a follow the path to the summit. About 1hr.
